Validation rules
The app enforces the following rules to ensure clean, consistent data. If any rule is broken, you will see an error message and the entry will not be saved until you fix it.

Rule	What it means	Error you will see
All fields are mandatory	Every field (except Comments) must be filled in	Mandatory fields left empty: [field names]
Dropdowns must be selected	You cannot leave a dropdown on “-- Select --”	Please select a value for: [field names]
No multiple spaces	Only one space between words is allowed	Multiple consecutive spaces found in: [field names]
No leading or trailing spaces	No spaces at the start or end of a value	Leading or trailing spaces found in: [field names]
HLD / IFM must be Confluence URLs	Must start with https://colesgroup.atlassian.net/	URL must begin with https://colesgroup.atlassian.net/ for: [field names]
Database Name prefix	Must start with DB_CORE_	Value must begin with DB_CORE_ for: Database Name
Expiration Date required if Encrypted	When Encrypted = YES, you must pick a date	Mandatory fields left empty: Expiration Date
No duplicate entries	Same Source System + Interface Name + Database Name + PSG Table Name cannot exist twice	An entry with this primary key combination already exists.
Character limit	Text fields allow up to 500 characters, Comments up to 2000	Field stops accepting input at the limit
Automatic uppercase	Source System, Interface Name, Database Name, PSG Table Name, and Stage Table Name are converted to uppercase when saved	No error — happens automatically

