Editing an entry
Expand the entry you want to edit
Click the Edit button
A dialog box opens with all fields pre-filled with the current values
Make your changes
Click Update to save, or Cancel to discard
The same validation rules apply when editing. The Engineer Email field is locked and cannot be changed.

If you change the key fields (Source System, Interface Name, Database Name, PSG Table Name) to values that match an existing entry, you will see an error preventing the duplicate.


Screenshot: Edit dialog

Deleting an entry
Deleting has a 3-step confirmation to prevent accidental deletions:

Click Delete on the entry
The button changes to Confirm? — click again if you are sure
The button changes to DELETE! (red) — click one final time to delete
At any point, click Cancel to abort the deletion.

Deleted entries are not permanently removed — they are marked as inactive in the system for audit purposes.


