Tips for clean data entry
Be consistent with naming — The app auto-uppercases key fields, but use the same naming conventions your team has agreed on
Use the correct Confluence URLs — Copy the full URL from your browser, not a shortened link
One interface per entry — Do not combine multiple interfaces into a single record
Use commas for multiple values — If a field needs multiple values (e.g., multiple source contacts), separate them with commas
Check for existing entries first — Before creating a new entry, use Tab 2 to search and make sure it does not already exist
Frequently Asked Questions
Q: I made a mistake in my entry. Can I fix it?
Yes. Go to the Existing Entries tab, find your entry, click Edit, and update the fields.

Q: I accidentally deleted an entry. Is it gone forever?
No. Deleted entries are soft-deleted (marked as inactive). Contact the Core Ops Engineering team to restore it if needed.

Q: Why can I not change the Engineer Email field?
This field is automatically set to your login email to ensure accurate tracking of who created or last modified each entry.

Q: Why is the Expiration Date field greyed out?
The Expiration Date only appears when you set Encrypted to YES. If Encrypted is NO, there is no expiration date to set.

Q: I am getting a “primary key already exists” error. What do I do?
This means an entry with the same Source System, Interface Name, Database Name, and PSG Table Name already exists. Search for it in Tab 2 — you may need to edit the existing entry instead of creating a new one.

Q: The app seems slow when I type in the search box.
The app queries the database as you type. If you experience slowness, try using the dropdown filters to narrow your results first, then search within the filtered set.

